name: Global X 0-3 Month T-Bill ETF
longDescription: CBIL will generally invest in Government of Canada Treasury Bills that are denominated in Canadian dollars with maturities of 90 days or less. CBIL is a money market fund within the definition set out in NI 81-102, and complies with all applicable requirements of NI 81-102, subject to any exemptive relief therefrom. The Manager will generally endeavour to maintain a target duration for CBIL, within a certain band, by employing rules-based security selection methodology and weighting. Securities will also be subject to a screening process to ensure sufficient liquidity and to mitigate transaction costs.
fulldescription: CBIL will generally invest in Government of Canada Treasury Bills that are denominated in Canadian dollars with maturities of 90 days or less. CBIL is a money market fund within the definition set out in NI 81-102, and complies with all applicable requirements of NI 81-102, subject to any exemptive relief therefrom. The Manager will generally endeavour to maintain a target duration for CBIL, within a certain band, by employing rules-based security selection methodology and weighting. Securities will also be subject to a screening process to ensure sufficient liquidity and to mitigate transaction costs. CBIL seeks to provide interest income through exposure to Government of Canada Treasury Bills with remaining maturities generally less than 3 months
